<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-RvTCMImvUwfZsEfU5zaAPw" name=",_x7hcUKM0EeC6tIhMGJuAIA" guid="-RvTCMImvUwfZsEfU5zaAPw" changeDate="2011-07-14T03:16:13.268-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The intent of the safety requirements specification is to identify each software based function whose failure could&#xD;
    lead to a violation of technical safety requirement that has been allocated to software. This is derived from the&#xD;
    technical safety concept and the systems specification.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If there are other functions (not related to the safety requirements) that are to be carried out by the same piece of&#xD;
    embedded software, these functions shall also be specified or a reference made to the specification.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Within the software safety requirements there should be enough information to allow the SW design and related&#xD;
    development, verification, validation and functional safety assessment activities to be carried out effectively.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    For more details the user is referred to ISO 26262, volume 6, clauses 6.4.2, 4 and 5.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The software safety specification can be derived (if employing a use case based approach) using &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../practice.tech.syseng.build_validate_uc.base-ibm/capabilitypatterns/val_uc_seq_95FC6A43.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_FWr3QXItEd6TqoTvu90UgA&quot;>Build and Validate Use Cases [Scenario Driven]&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;if&amp;nbsp;the focus of the use&#xD;
    cases is&amp;nbsp;safety based. From this the HW/SW interfaces can also be derived.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To develop a complete and consistent specification for the SW of the item that should be consistent with the technical&#xD;
safety concept and the system design specification.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
